tafsir[3]{c,v,t}:
  73,1,"And from his narration on the authority of Ibn 'Abbas that he said concerning Allah's saying (O thou wrapped up in your raiment!): '(O thou wrapped up in your raiment!) He is referring here to Muhammad (pbuh) who wrapped himself up in his raiment in order to pray."
  73,7,"(Lo! thou hast by day) O Muhammad (a chain of business) a long period of time to attend to your needs."
  73,18,"(The very heaven being then) when the children turn grey; and it is said: due to the descent of the command of the Lord and the angels (rent asunder. His promise) regarding the resurrection (is to be fulfilled) is to take place."